g.aria-label: A typeset page body (a list of nodes) resulting from the latest page break. It contains some mark nodes.
The typeset page body is pre-processed to determine values for the three (global) mark variables: \topmark, \botmark and \firstmark.
Page body is sent for "initial pre-processing" of its content, which includes looking for mark nodes.
The output routine uses the value of \topmark, \firstmark and \botmark to create headers and footers.
All three mark variables, \topmark, \botmark and \firstmark, are global variables so their data is accessible to any commands contained in the output routine.
The finished page is written out to the PDF file.
